Commentary Text: Ferguson to Pollard, out Pollard Run Out!! This is turning out to be a brilliant final over for KKR. Ferguson just misses the wide yorker, Pollard drives the slot ball really hard, but he picks out Morgan to perfection at extra cover. Should have retained strike because there was no way Pollard could have got home after standing deep in the crease and the weight on the back foot. Morgan throws it to the bowler, who brilliantly does well to run back to the stumps. Kudos to that presence of mind. Pollard could have got away with a direct-hit attempt. Pollard run out (Morgan/Ferguson) 21(15) [4s-2 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Prasidh to de Kock, out Caught by Narine!! This is a very smart bowling from Prasidh. For some reason de Kock took his off-side play out and only looked to target mid-wicket. Prasidh took pace off on this length ball and a mishit went straight to mid-wicket. Pressure on MI now that the set, but tired QdK walks off. de Kock c Narine b Prasidh 55(42) [4s-4 6s-3]

Commentary Text: Prasidh to Suryakumar Yadav, out Caught by Karthik!! This is a very good little phase for KKR. Morgan was bold enough to bowl out both his mystery spinners probably thinking - if they get a wicket, great, but if they can build pressure for the rest of the bowlers to take over, that is fine too. And first ball of a challenging phase Prasidh has prised out the big wicket of SKY with a ball that he is good with. On a length and getting it to seam away, SKY playing a bit across the line towards mid-on and getting a thick edg to DK. In fact was looking to play straight only but used hit wrist a bit there to nick off. Suryakumar Yadav c Karthik b Prasidh 5(10)

Commentary Text: Bumrah to Shubman Gill, out Bowled!! He's knocked him over! Gill chops on! A slower one that's cutting back in, leaves a massive gap with the bat coming down from gully, and gets a bit of inside edge on it, as it crashes into the stumps. Bumrah is delighted, and punches the air. Mumbai's pride had been hurt in the last three overs, and Bumrah has brought some redemption with this wicket. Shubman Gill b Bumrah 13(9) [4s-1 6s-1]
